  "response_text": "# Grilled Lemon Herb Chicken with Roasted Vegetables\n\n## Ingredients\n\n**For the chicken:**\n- 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\n- 3 tbsp olive oil\n- Juice of 2 lemons\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 tsp dried oregano\n- 1 tsp dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n**For the vegetables:**\n- 2 cups broccoli florets\n- 2 cups Brussels sprouts, halved\n- 1 bell pepper, chopped\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Marinate the chicken** (30 minutes or more):\n   - Mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, and thyme\n   - Coat chicken and refrigerate\n\n2. **Prepare vegetables**:\n   - Toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper\n   - Spread on a baking sheet\n\n3. **Cook**:\n   - Roast vegetables at 400°F for 20 minutes\n   - Grill or pan-sear chicken 6-7 minutes per side until cooked through\n   - Add to vegetables and bake together 5 minutes\n\n4. **Rest and serve**: Let chicken rest 5 minutes before serving\n\n## Nutrition Highlights\n- High in lean protein\n- Rich in vitamins and fiber\n- Low in calories (~350 per serving)\n- Healthy fats from olive oil\n\n**Serves: 4 | Prep time: 10 min | Cook time: 25 min**",
